                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.334,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has our opinion in Case 13-9972, Rodriguez v. United States."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.334,
                        "stop": 341.472,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.334,
                                "stop": 31.093,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Does the Fourth Amendment, which shields people from unreasonable searches and seizures by law enforcement personnel, permit police on stopping a vehicle for a traffic offense to detain the car and driver to seek evidence of crimes unrelated to the traffic offense?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.093,
                                "stop": 42.225,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Our answer, police may not prolong detention of car and driver beyond the time reasonably required to address the traffic violation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.225,
                                "stop": 51.164,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We so stated 10 years ago in Illinois v. Caballes and today adhere to the line drawn in Caballes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.164,
                                "stop": 67.084,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The episode in controversy, Officer Struble, a K-9 officer policing Nebraska roads, pulled Rodriguez over for driving on a highway shoulder in violation of Nebraska\u0027s traffic code."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.084,
                                "stop": 75.068,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "After attending to everything related to the traffic stop, Struble handled Rodriguez a written warning."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.068,
                                "stop": 80.706,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "He then asked Rodriguez for permission to walk his dog around the vehicle."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.706,
                                "stop": 88.523,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "When Rodriguez refused consent, Struble detained him, pending the arrival of a second officer."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.523,
                                "stop": 97.061,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "After that officer arrived Struble retrieved his dog, who alerted to the presence of drugs in Rodriguez\u0027s car."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.061,
                                "stop": 103.598,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Seven or eight minutes elapsed from issuance of the warning until the dog alerted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.598,
                                "stop": 110.736,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Indicted on federal drug charges Rodriguez moved to suppress the evidence seized from the car."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.736,
                                "stop": 122.719,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The magistrate judge, an intern of the District Court, found that the traffic stop had been prolonged without reasonable suspicion in order to conduct the dog sniff."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.719,
                                "stop": 136.308,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But they ruled under controlling Eight Circuit precedent, extending the stop by seven or eight minutes ranked as a de minimis intrusion and was therefore permissible."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.308,
                                "stop": 144.665,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Agreeing that the evidence detected by the dog was admissible, the Court of Appeals affirmed Rodriguez\u0027s drug conviction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.665,
                                "stop": 147.839,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We vacate the Court of Appeals judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.839,
                                "stop": 163.469,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Court held in Illinois v. Caballes that a dog sniff conducted during a lawful traffic stop is compatible with the Fourth Amendment if the sniff does not lengthen the roadside detention."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.469,
                                "stop": 176.237,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The tolerable duration of a traffic stop is determined by its mission, which is to address the traffic violation that warranted the stop and attend to related safety concerns."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.237,
                                "stop": 205.738,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "As we cautioned in Caballes, a traffic stop does not license police to pursue unrelated investigations that prolong attention of car and driver beyond the time it takes to complete the stop\u0027s traffic centered mission. That mission typically includes checking the driver\u0027s license, determining whether there are outstanding warrants against the driver, and inspecting the automobile\u0027s registration and proof of insurance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 205.738,
                                "stop": 210.954,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "These checks serve the same objective as enforcement of the traffic code."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 210.954,
                                "stop": 217.912,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They are viewed to ensuring that vehicles on the road are operated safely and responsibly."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 217.912,
                                "stop": 225.417,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "A dog sniff, unlike those stock inquiries, lacks the same tie to roadway safety."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 225.417,
                                "stop": 231.787,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "For its de minimis rule the Eighth Circuit relied on this Court\u0027s decision in Pennsylvania v. Mimms."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 231.787,
                                "stop": 242.02,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "There we held that as a safety precaution an officer may order a driver to exit a lawfully stopped vehicle."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 242.02,
                                "stop": 249.367,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The officer\u0027s safety interest in Mimms however stemmed from the danger of the stop itself."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 249.367,
                                "stop": 258.868,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The dog sniffing contrast aims to detect unrelated crimes and thus detours from the officer\u0027s traffic control mission."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 258.868,
                                "stop": 271.453,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The government asks us to uphold the Eighth Circuit\u0027s judgment by focusing on whether the total duration of the stop was reasonable in comparison to other traffic stops involving similar circumstances."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 271.453,
                                "stop": 283.23,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In effect, the government argues that by completing all traffic related tasks quickly, an officer can earn bonus time to pursue an unrelated criminal inquiry."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 283.23,
                                "stop": 295.617,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We look instead to the officer\u0027s actual conduct, did he, as Officer Struble testified, get all the business of the stop out of the way before tacking on a dog sniff?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 295.617,
                                "stop": 308.026,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "As we indicated in Caballes and hold today, a traffic stop becomes unlawful if prolonged beyond the time in fact needed to complete all traffic based inquires."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 308.026,
                                "stop": 325.816,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Although we vacate the Eighth Circuit\u0027s judgment, we remand the case for consideration of a question not reached by the Court of Appeals, did the police have a reasonable basis independent of the traffic offense to suspect that Rodriguez was engaged in drug dealing?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 325.816,
                                "stop": 331.124,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justices Kennedy, Thomas, and Alito have each filed dissenting opinions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 331.124,
                                "stop": 341.472,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has joined Justice Thomas\u0027 dissent, as has Justice Kennedy, save for Part 3."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
